From: PanicOS <panicos@localhost>
Date: Sat, 24 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] clk: sunxi-ng: fix pll-audio-hs SDM table rates for H616

ccu_nm_set_rate() multiplies the requested rate by fixed_post_div before
comparing against the SDM table (drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu_nm.c line 178):

    if (nm->common.features & CCU_FEATURE_FIXED_POSTDIV)
        rate = rate * nm->fixed_post_div;  /* ×2 BEFORE SDM check */

    if (ccu_sdm_helper_has_rate(..., rate)) { ... }

pll-audio-hs has fixed_post_div=2, so when the AHUB driver requests
98304000 Hz the SDM check compares 196608000 against the table entries
{90316800, 98304000}.  The comparison always fails, SDM stays disabled,
integer-only N/M is used, and the PLL fails to lock (ccu_helper_wait_for_lock
WARN_ON at ~500ms).  The PLL stays at whatever rate U-Boot left it at
(688 MHz on RG35XX Pro), causing HDMI audio to play at ~80-85% speed.

Fix: store VCO rates (= output × fixed_post_div = output × 2) in the table
so that ccu_nm_set_rate's pre-multiplied comparison hits the right entry.
ccu_nm_recalc_rate already divides the table rate by fixed_post_div when
returning the clock's observable output rate, so recalc_rate is unaffected.

VCO rates:
  48 kHz path:  98304000 Hz output × 2 = 196608000 Hz VCO  (N=40, M=5)
  44.1 kHz path: 90316800 Hz output × 2 = 180633600 Hz VCO  (N=22, M=3)

Signed-off-by: PanicOS <panicos@localhost>
---
 drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun50i-h616.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun50i-h616.c b/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun50i-h616.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun50i-h616.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-sun50i-h616.c
@@ -223,8 +223,8 @@
  * frequencies with less error.
  */
 static struct ccu_sdm_setting pll_audio_sdm_table[] = {
-	{ .rate = 90316800, .pattern = 0xc001288d, .m = 3, .n = 22 },
-	{ .rate = 98304000, .pattern = 0xc001eb85, .m = 5, .n = 40 },
+	{ .rate = 180633600, .pattern = 0xc001288d, .m = 3, .n = 22 },
+	{ .rate = 196608000, .pattern = 0xc001eb85, .m = 5, .n = 40 },
 };

 #define SUN50I_H616_PLL_AUDIO_REG	0x078
